  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Clinicians are indispensable to synthesizing relevant context and offering patient counseling and subsequent care.",
    "Furthermore, given the enhanced accuracy of diagnosis when integrating AI into decisionmaking, the future of dermatology will likely entail human-computer collaboration (98).",
    "Embedding Collective Human Intelligence (CoHI) or even swarm intelligence (CoHI with interaction between participating humans) as checkpoints within an AI model may help overcome the limited ability of AI to contextualize and generalize (99).",
    "When interacting with AI, potential cognitive errors and biases may be exacerbated, especially when there is discordance in diagnosis between clinicians and AI (100).",
    "The use of AI introduces a new kind of bias called automation bias, in which humans tend to unquestioningly trust automated decisions from AI (100)."
  ],
